The paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for object recognition, specifically using recurrent neural networks instead of the convolutional layer. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed network on three widely-used benchmark datasets, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.NE, cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves image processing and recognition, which could also place it in the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
